properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 26 at 12:28PM PST until January 27 at 6:00AM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Areas of northwest to north winds 20 to 35 mph with
gusts to 50 mph.

* WHERE...Santa Barbara County Mountains.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and
make driving difficult, especially for driver of high profile
vehicles. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power
outages may result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Gusty winds will affect travel on
Highways 101 and 154, including Gaviota Pass and San Marcos
Pass.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects such as lawn furniture.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM PST MONDAY
